      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, I see how the general statement is incorrect, adjusting my grokage here:\n\n  * \u0027static\u0027 affects external visibility, iff the compiler decides to not inline\n  * \u0027inline\u0027 is a hint, but doesn\u0027t really guarantee inlining\n\nSince this is CU-local and we only instantiate once (per type), is it correct to reduce the statement to \"in this particular case, the qualifiers will make no difference\"?  Or is it still a stretch?\n\n(not arguing for dropping them anymore, just clarifying my understanding)",
